{
  "texts": [
    "The effect of the temperature parameter on a hypothetical probability distribution for the next token is illustrated in Fig. 2.",
    "In accordance with likely societal use, we set the temperature parameter to the default intermediate value of 1.0 (OpenAI, 2023a).",
    "Historically, GPT-3.5's default temperature setting of 1.0 has generally been thought to output answers that are not predetermined.",
    "This can be seen from OpenAI's instruction regarding the temperature parameter: \"higher values [of temperature] like 0.8 will make the output more random, while lower values like 0.2 will make it more focused and deterministic\" (OpenAI, 2023a).",
    "Thus, at the time of pre-registration, we had not considered the possibility that all or nearly all ~ 1000 runs of the default temperature setting of GPT-3.5 might answer one of our survey questions in a predetermined way."
  ]
}